#: src/01-authorization.md:3
msgid ""
"This page explains how Mycelium decides whether a request is allowed to "
"proceed."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:7
msgid "The short version"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:9
msgid "Mycelium uses a **two-layer** approach:"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:11
msgid ""
"**Gateway layer** — coarse checks at the route level (\"is this user logged "
"in? do they have the right role?\"). If the check fails, the request is "
"rejected before reaching your service."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:14
msgid ""
"**Downstream layer** — fine-grained checks inside your service, using the "
"identity that Mycelium injects (\"does this user have write access to _this "
"specific resource_?\")."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:17
msgid ""
"Think of it like a building: Mycelium is the security desk at the entrance "
"(checks your ID and badge before letting you through the door). Your service "
"is the room inside — it gets to decide what the person can do once they're "
"in."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:23
msgid "The gateway layer"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:25
msgid ""
"When a request arrives, Mycelium matches it against the configured route. "
"Each route belongs to a **security group** that defines the minimum "
"requirements:"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:28 src/06-downstream-apis.md:223
msgid "Security group"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:28
msgid "What Mycelium checks"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:30
msgid "`public`"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:30
msgid "Nothing — anyone can pass"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:31 src/06-downstream-apis.md:225
msgid "`authenticated`"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:31
msgid "Valid JWT or connection string"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:32 src/06-downstream-apis.md:226
msgid "`protected`"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:32
msgid "Valid token + resolved profile"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:33 src/06-downstream-apis.md:227
msgid "`protectedByRoles`"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:33
msgid "Valid token + user has one of the listed roles"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:35
msgid ""
"If the check passes, Mycelium forwards the request to your service and "
"injects the user's identity as HTTP headers."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:40
msgid "What gets injected"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:42
msgid "Depending on the security group, your service receives:"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:44
msgid "Header"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:44
msgid "When injected"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:44
msgid "Contains"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:46 src/06-downstream-apis.md:223
msgid "`x-mycelium-email`"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:46
msgid "`authenticated` or higher"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:46
msgid "The authenticated user's email"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:47 src/06-downstream-apis.md:223
msgid "`x-mycelium-profile`"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:47
msgid "`protected` or higher"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:47
msgid "Full identity context (see below)"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:49
msgid ""
"The profile is a compressed JSON object carrying: account ID, tenant "
"memberships, roles, and access scopes. Your service reads it and can make "
"resource-level decisions without querying the gateway or doing its own "
"authentication."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:55
msgid "The downstream layer"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:57
msgid ""
"Once a request is inside your service, you use the profile to decide what "
"the user can do with a specific resource. The profile exposes a fluent API "
"for narrowing the access context:"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:60
msgid ""
"```\n"
"profile\n"
"  .on_tenant(tenant_id)     # focus on this tenant\n"
"  .on_account(account_id)   # focus on this account\n"
"  .with_write_access()      # must have write permission\n"
"  .with_roles([\"manager\"])  # must have manager role\n"
"  .get_related_account_or_error()  # returns error if no match\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:69
msgid ""
"Each step narrows — never expands — the set of permissions. If any step "
"finds no match, the chain returns an error and you return 403 to your caller."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:72
msgid "This design means:"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:73
msgid "Access decisions are explicit and auditable."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:74
msgid "No implicit \"superuser\" paths that bypass checks."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:75
msgid "Your service never needs to call Mycelium again to validate permissions."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:79
msgid "Reference"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:81
msgid "Formal classification"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:83
msgid "Mycelium's model spans three standard paradigms:"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:85
msgid ""
"**RBAC** (Role-Based Access Control) — used declaratively at the gateway "
"level (security groups with role lists)."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:86
msgid ""
"**ABAC** (Attribute-Based Access Control) — the profile carries attributes "
"(tenant, account, scope) used in downstream decisions."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:87
msgid ""
"**FBAC** (Feature-Based Access Control) — the dominant model; access "
"decisions are made close to the resource using the full contextual chain."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:89
msgid "Design principles"
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:91
msgid ""
"Authentication, identity enrichment, and authorization are strictly "
"separated."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:92
msgid ""
"Capabilities are progressively reduced — the chain never grants more than "
"the token allows."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:93
msgid "No global policies that silently override explicit checks."
msgstr ""

#: src/01-authorization.md:94
msgid ""
"Each authorization decision is a discrete, loggable event (resource, action, "
"context, outcome)."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:3
msgid ""
"This page covers the three ways users authenticate with Mycelium and how to "
"create service-to-service tokens."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:8
msgid "Magic link (email login)"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:10
msgid ""
"Magic link is the default authentication method. No passwords required — the "
"user enters their email and receives a one-time link."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:13 src/12-response-callbacks.md:13
#: src/16-webhooks.md:10
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:15
msgid ""
"```\n"
"User enters email\n"
"    ↓\n"
"POST /_adm/beginners/users/magic-link/request\n"
"    ↓\n"
"Mycelium sends a login email with a one-time link\n"
"    ↓\n"
"User clicks the link → GET /_adm/beginners/users/magic-link/display/{token}\n"
"    ↓\n"
"POST /_adm/beginners/users/magic-link/verify  (with the token)\n"
"    ↓\n"
"Response: { \"token\": \"jwt...\", \"type\": \"Bearer\" }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:29
msgid "Enabling it"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:31
msgid "Internal authentication must be enabled in `config.toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:33
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[auth]\n"
"internal = \"enabled\"\n"
"jwtSecret = \"your-secret\"\n"
"jwtExpiresIn = 86400\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:40
msgid ""
"SMTP must also be configured so Mycelium can send the email. See "
"[Configuration](./04-configuration.md#smtp-and-queue--email)."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:42
msgid "Using the JWT"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:44
msgid "After login, include the JWT in every request:"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:50
msgid "The JWT is valid for `jwtExpiresIn` seconds (default: 24 hours)."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:54
msgid "Two-factor authentication (2FA / TOTP)"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:56
msgid ""
"Users can add a second factor using any TOTP authenticator app (Google "
"Authenticator, Authy, 1Password, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:59
msgid "Enabling 2FA (user journey)"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:61
msgid "**Step 1 — Start activation:**"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:68 src/11-authentication-flows.md:144
msgid "Response:"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:71
msgid "\"totpUrl\""
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:71
msgid ""
"\"otpauth://totp/MyApp:user@example.com?secret=BASE32SECRET&issuer=MyApp\""
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:75
msgid ""
"The user scans the `totpUrl` in their authenticator app (or adds the secret "
"manually)."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:77
msgid "**Step 2 — Confirm activation:**"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:79
msgid ""
"```http\n"
"POST /_adm/beginners/users/totp/validate-app\n"
"Authorization: Bearer <jwt>\n"
"Content-Type: application/json\n"
"\n"
"{ \"token\": \"123456\" }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:87
msgid ""
"The `token` is the 6-digit code shown in the authenticator app. This "
"confirms that the app is correctly configured and activates 2FA on the "
"account."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:90
msgid "Logging in with 2FA"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:92
msgid ""
"When 2FA is enabled, the magic link login response includes `totp_required: "
"true`. The client must then call:"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:95
msgid ""
"```http\n"
"POST /_adm/beginners/users/totp/check-token\n"
"Authorization: Bearer <jwt>\n"
"Content-Type: application/json\n"
"\n"
"{ \"token\": \"123456\" }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:103
msgid "Only after a successful TOTP check does the session have full access."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:105
msgid "Disabling 2FA"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:107
msgid ""
"```http\n"
"POST /_adm/beginners/users/totp/disable\n"
"Authorization: Bearer <jwt>\n"
"Content-Type: application/json\n"
"\n"
"{ \"token\": \"123456\" }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:115
msgid "Requires a valid TOTP token to confirm the user's intent."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:119
msgid "Connection strings (service tokens)"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:121
msgid ""
"A connection string is a long-lived API token tied to a specific account, "
"tenant, and role. Use them for:"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:124
msgid ""
"**Machine-to-machine calls** — scripts, cron jobs, or services that don't "
"have a user session."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:125
msgid ""
"**Telegram Mini Apps** — the gateway issues a connection string when a user "
"logs in via Telegram (see [Alternative Identity "
"Providers](./10-alternative-idps.md))."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:127
msgid "**Long-running sessions** — when the standard JWT expiry is too short."
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:129
msgid "Creating a connection string"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:131
msgid ""
"```http\n"
"POST /_adm/beginners/tokens\n"
"Authorization: Bearer <jwt>\n"
"Content-Type: application/json\n"
"\n"
"{\n"
"  \"tenantId\": \"a3f1e2d0-1234-4abc-8def-000000000001\",\n"
"  \"accountId\": \"b5e2f3a1-5678-4def-9abc-000000000002\",\n"
"  \"role\": \"manager\",\n"
"  \"expiresAt\": \"2027-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:147 src/10-alternative-idps.md:283
msgid "\"connectionString\""
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:147
msgid "\"acc=<uuid>;tid=<uuid>;r=manager;edt=2027-01-01T00:00:00Z;sig=<hmac>\""
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:148 src/10-alternative-idps.md:284
msgid "\"expiresAt\""
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:148
msgid "\"2027-01-01T00:00:00Z\""
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:152
msgid "Listing your connection strings"
msgstr ""

#: src/11-authentication-flows.md:159
msgid "Using a connection string"
