#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide explains how to register a backend service with Mycelium and "
"control who can access it."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:5
msgid ""
"All service configuration lives in `settings/config.toml` under "
"`[api.services]`. Restart the gateway after any change."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:10
msgid "Registering a service"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:12
msgid "The simplest possible registration:"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:14
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[api.services]\n"
"\n"
"[[my-service]]\n"
"host = \"localhost:3000\"\n"
"protocol = \"http\"\n"
"\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"public\"\n"
"path = \"/api/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\", \"POST\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:27
msgid ""
"This tells Mycelium: \"Any GET or POST to `/api/*` should be forwarded to "
"`localhost:3000`.\" No authentication required — anyone can reach this route."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:30
msgid ""
"The service name (`my-service`) becomes part of how you identify the service "
"internally. It does not affect the URL path; the path comes from the `path` "
"field."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:35
msgid "Choosing a security group"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:37
msgid ""
"The `group` field on each route controls what Mycelium requires before "
"forwarding the request."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:39
msgid "`public` — No authentication"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:41
msgid ""
"Anyone can access the route. Use for health checks, public APIs, and "
"Telegram webhooks."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:43
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"public\"\n"
"path = \"/health\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:50
msgid "`authenticated` — Valid login token required"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:52
msgid ""
"The user must be logged in. Mycelium injects their email in "
"`x-mycelium-email`."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:54
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"authenticated\"\n"
"path = \"/profile\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\", \"PUT\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:61
msgid "`protected` — Full identity required"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:63
msgid ""
"The user must be logged in and have a resolved profile. Mycelium injects the "
"full profile in `x-mycelium-profile`. Use this when your service needs to "
"make fine-grained decisions (e.g. \"can this user access this specific "
"resource?\")."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:67
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"protected\"\n"
"path = \"/dashboard/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:74
msgid "`protectedByRoles` — Specific roles required"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:76
msgid ""
"Only users with at least one of the listed roles can pass. All others get "
"403."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:78
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = { protectedByRoles = [{ slug = \"admin\" }, { slug = \"super-admin\" "
"}] }\n"
"path = \"/admin/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"ALL\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:85
msgid "You can also require a specific permission level:"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:87
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = { protectedByRoles = [{ slug = \"editor\", permission = \"write\" }] "
"}\n"
"path = \"/content/edit/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"]\n"
"\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = { protectedByRoles = [{ slug = \"viewer\", permission = \"read\" }] "
"}\n"
"path = \"/content/view/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:101
msgid "Multiple routes on one service"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:103
msgid ""
"Each `[[service-name.path]]` block adds a route. Mix security groups freely:"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:105
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[user-service]]\n"
"host = \"users.internal:4000\"\n"
"protocol = \"http\"\n"
"\n"
"[[user-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"authenticated\"\n"
"path = \"/users/me\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\", \"PUT\"]\n"
"\n"
"[[user-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"protected\"\n"
"path = \"/users/preferences\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\", \"POST\"]\n"
"\n"
"[[user-service.path]]\n"
"group = { protectedByRoles = [{ slug = \"admin\" }] }\n"
"path = \"/users/admin/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"ALL\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:128
msgid "Authenticating Mycelium to your service (secrets)"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:130
msgid ""
"If your downstream service requires a token or API key from the caller, "
"define a secret and reference it on the route."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:133
msgid "**Query parameter:**"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:134
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[legacy-api]]\n"
"host = \"legacy.internal:8080\"\n"
"protocol = \"http\"\n"
"\n"
"[[legacy-api.secret]]\n"
"name = \"api-key\"\n"
"queryParameter = { name = \"token\", token = { env = \"LEGACY_API_KEY\" } }\n"
"\n"
"[[legacy-api.path]]\n"
"group = \"public\"\n"
"path = \"/legacy/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"GET\"]\n"
"secretName = \"api-key\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:150
msgid "**Authorization header:**"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:151
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[protected-api.secret]]\n"
"name = \"bearer-token\"\n"
"authorizationHeader = { name = \"Authorization\", prefix = \"Bearer \", "
"token = { vault = { path = \"myc/services/api\", key = \"token\" } } }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:159
msgid "Load balancing across multiple hosts"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:161
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[api-service]]\n"
"hosts = [\"api-01.example.com:8080\", \"api-02.example.com:8080\"]\n"
"protocol = \"https\"\n"
"\n"
"[[api-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"protected\"\n"
"path = \"/api/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"ALL\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:174
msgid "Webhook routes — identity from request body"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:176
msgid ""
"Some callers (like Telegram) don't send a JWT. Instead, the user's identity "
"is in the request body. Use `identitySource` to handle this."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:179
msgid ""
"**Requires `allowedSources`** — before parsing the body, Mycelium checks "
"that the `Host` header matches an allowed source. This prevents attackers "
"from forging webhook calls."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:182
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[telegram-bot]]\n"
"host = \"bot-service:3000\"\n"
"protocol = \"http\"\n"
"allowedSources = [\"api.telegram.org\"]\n"
"\n"
"[[telegram-bot.path]]\n"
"group = \"protected\"\n"
"path = \"/telegram/webhook\"\n"
"methods = [\"POST\"]\n"
"identitySource = \"telegram\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:195
msgid ""
"With this config, Mycelium extracts the Telegram user ID from the message "
"body, looks up the linked Mycelium account, and injects `x-mycelium-profile` "
"before forwarding. If the user hasn't linked their account, Mycelium returns "
"401 and the message is not forwarded."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:199
msgid ""
"See [Alternative Identity Providers](./10-alternative-idps.md) for the full "
"Telegram setup journey."
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:203
msgid "Service discovery (AI agents)"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:205
msgid ""
"Set `discoverable = true` to make a service visible to AI agents and "
"LLM-based tooling:"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:207
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[data-service]]\n"
"host = \"data.internal:5000\"\n"
"protocol = \"http\"\n"
"discoverable = true\n"
"description = \"Customer data API\"\n"
"openapiPath = \"/api/openapi.json\"\n"
"healthCheckPath = \"/health\"\n"
"capabilities = [\"customer-search\", \"order-history\"]\n"
"serviceType = \"rest-api\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:221
msgid "What headers does my service receive?"
msgstr ""

#: src/06-downstream-apis.md:225 src/06-downstream-apis.md:226
