#: src/10-alternative-idps.md:432
msgid ""
"```\n"
"acme-hr  (Telegram configured)          acme-operations  (no Telegram "
"config)\n"
"   │                                            │\n"
"   │  Maria links via HR Mini App              │  Operations has a support "
"bot\n"
"   │  → Telegram ID 98765432                   │  → route: identitySource = "
"\"telegram\"\n"
"   │    stored on Maria's personal account     │\n"
"   │                                            │  Telegram sends update "
"with from.id 98765432\n"
"   │                                            │  → Mycelium finds Maria "
"globally ✓\n"
"   │                                            │  → x-mycelium-profile "
"injected ✓\n"
"   │                                            │\n"
"   │  Maria cannot link via operations ✗       │  Maria cannot login via "
"Telegram here ✗\n"
"   │  Maria cannot login via Telegram here ✗   │  (no bot token to verify "
"initData)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/10-alternative-idps.md:446
msgid ""
"**In practice:** If you are building a webhook-only integration (Use Case B) "
"for a tenant, you do not need to configure Telegram for that tenant — as "
"long as users have linked in some other tenant. If you need login (Use Case "
"A) for that tenant, the tenant must have its own bot and must complete the "
"admin provisioning step."
