#: src/13-mcp.md:1
msgid "MCP — AI Agent Integration"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:3
msgid ""
"Mycelium exposes a **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** endpoint that lets AI "
"assistants (Claude, GPT, and any MCP-compatible agent) call your downstream "
"APIs as tools — without needing direct access to your services."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:9
msgid "What is MCP?"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:11
msgid ""
"MCP is an open protocol for connecting AI assistants to external tools and "
"data. With Mycelium's MCP support, an AI agent can:"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:14
msgid "**Discover** which operations your downstream services expose."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:15
msgid "**Call** those operations on behalf of an authenticated user."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:16
msgid ""
"**Receive** the responses and incorporate them into a response to the user."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:18
msgid ""
"The AI never bypasses Mycelium's authentication or authorization. Every tool "
"call is subject to the same security checks as a direct API request from a "
"client."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:25
msgid "For MCP to discover operations, your downstream services must:"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:27
msgid "Expose an **OpenAPI spec** at a known path."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:28
msgid ""
"Be registered in Mycelium's config with `discoverable = true` and "
"`openapiPath` set."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:30
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[my-service]]\n"
"host = \"api.internal:4000\"\n"
"protocol = \"http\"\n"
"discoverable = true\n"
"openapiPath = \"/api/openapi.json\"\n"
"description = \"Customer data API\"\n"
"capabilities = [\"customer-search\", \"order-history\"]\n"
"\n"
"[[my-service.path]]\n"
"group = \"protected\"\n"
"path = \"/api/*\"\n"
"methods = [\"ALL\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:47
msgid "The MCP endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:53
msgid "This single endpoint handles all MCP JSON-RPC requests. It supports:"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:55
msgid "MCP method"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:55
msgid "What it does"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:57
msgid "`initialize`"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:57
msgid "Returns Mycelium's MCP server info and capabilities"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:58
msgid "`tools/list`"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:58
msgid "Returns all operations discovered from `discoverable` services"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:59
msgid "`tools/call`"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:59
msgid "Executes a specific operation through the gateway"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:63
msgid "How tool calls work"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:65
msgid "When an AI calls `tools/call`, Mycelium:"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:67
msgid "Resolves the operation to the registered downstream service."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:68
msgid ""
"Validates the caller's token (forwarded from the original MCP request "
"header)."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:69
msgid ""
"Forwards the call through the gateway — including profile injection and all "
"security checks."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:70
msgid "Returns the downstream response as a tool result."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:72
msgid ""
"The AI passes its `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` or "
"`x-mycelium-connection-string` header in the MCP request, and Mycelium "
"forwards it when calling the downstream service."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:77
msgid "Connecting an AI assistant to Mycelium"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:79
msgid "Point the AI agent's MCP server URL to your Mycelium instance:"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:81
msgid ""
"```\n"
"http://your-gateway:8080/mcp\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:85
msgid "In Claude Desktop's MCP configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:89
msgid "\"mcpServers\""
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:90
msgid "\"mycelium\""
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:91
msgid "\"http://your-gateway:8080/mcp\""
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:97
msgid ""
"The assistant will authenticate as the user whose token is configured, and "
"will only be able to call operations that user is authorized to access."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:102
msgid "Tool naming"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:104
msgid ""
"Mycelium builds tool names deterministically from the service name and "
"OpenAPI operation path: `{service_name}__{http_method}__{path_slug}`."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:107
msgid ""
"For example, an operation `GET /api/customers/{id}` on service "
"`customer-api` becomes the tool name `customer-api__get__api_customers_id`."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:112
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:114
msgid ""
"MCP support requires `discoverable = true` and a valid `openapiPath` on at "
"least one service."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:115
msgid ""
"Operations on non-discoverable services are never exposed to the MCP "
"endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: src/13-mcp.md:116
msgid ""
"The MCP endpoint itself does not require authentication to connect, but "
"individual `tools/call` requests are forwarded with the caller's token — so "
"unauthorized calls will be rejected with `401`/`403` by the downstream "
"route's security group."
msgstr ""

#: src/14-json-rpc.md:3
msgid ""
"Mycelium exposes all administrative operations through a **JSON-RPC 2.0** "
"interface at `POST /_adm/rpc`. This endpoint accepts both single requests "
"and batched arrays of requests."
msgstr ""

#: src/14-json-rpc.md:6
msgid ""
"The JSON-RPC interface mirrors the REST admin API — every operation "
"available through the REST routes is also available as a JSON-RPC method. "
"Prefer JSON-RPC when building programmatic clients, automation scripts, or "
"AI agent integrations."
msgstr ""

#: src/14-json-rpc.md:12
msgid "Transport"
msgstr ""

#: src/14-json-rpc.md:20
